definition.value: A member of the class of furans that is furan substituted by a 3-ethoxy-3-oxoprop-1-en-1-yl group at position 2.
A sulfur-containing amino acid obtained by the oxidation of two cysteine molecules which are then linked via a disulfide bond.
A disaccharide derivative that is the 2"-O-beta-D-glucosyl derivative of isovitexin .
